REPUBLIC OF BOTSWANA

INSTRUMENT OF ACCESSION

CONVENTION RELATING TO INTERNATIONAL EXHIBITIONS

WHEREAS the Convention Relating to International Exhibitions was signed at Paris on 22nd November 1928;

AND WHEREAS the said Convention was supplemented by the Protocols of 10t May 1948, 16th November 1966, and 30th November 1972, the Amendment of 24'h June 1982, and the Amendment of 31st May 1988;

AND WHEREAS the said Convention has entered into force;

AND WHEREAS Botswana is not a signatory;

AND WHEREAS it is provided in Article 35 of the said Convention that the Convention shall be open for accession by any State which is a member of the United Nations, or any

State which is not a member of the United Nations but which is a Party to the Statute of the international Court of Justice or any State which is a member of one of the specialised agencies of the United Nations or the International Atomic Energy Agency and also by any

State whose application for accession is approved by a two-thirds majority of the

Contracting Parties which have the right to vote in the General Assembly of the Bureau.

AND WHEREAS Botswana is a member of the United Nations;

AND WHEREAS after examining the aforesaid Convention, I am satisfied that it is in the interest of the Republic of Botswana to accede to the aforesaid Convention;
